fields.title: Keep your things chilled with - Cooler Bags & Ice Packs
fields.body_html:
If you choose we will include a cooler bag with 2 ice gel packs with any order requiring goods kept chilled. The charge for this is $12.00. Leave them out with your box and we will rotate them when we next deliver to you. 

Our Cooler Bags and Ice Packs provide protection from the heat for all your chilled goods.  

The cooler bags are made from environmentally friendly Lightweight PET with heaps of room and a handy zip, durable and reusable, the size is 330mm(w) x 370mm(h) x 235mm(d).

The ice packs are a water based biodegradable, non toxic gel refrigerant sealed in a two ply laminated nylon pouch which is specifically designed for shipping temperature sensitive products. Reusable, biodegradable & non toxic gel. 

If you prefer not to use the cooler bag system we still carefully care for your items that require chilling by using recycle-able plastic bags along with the ice gel packs.

Once opened, UHT (Ultra Heat Treated) milk must be refrigerated and used within seven days.

fields.title: Radish
Recipe - Beetroot & Apple Salad
fields.body_html:
Ingredients (serves 4)

2 apples - thinly sliced

4 celery stalks with leaves - thinly sliced

1 spring onion - minced

1 lemon - juiced

1 beetroot - peeled & sliced into matchsticks

1 tsp sugar

3 tablespoons walnuts - chopped

3 tablespoons olive oil

salt  & pepper

1/2 iceberg lettuce

Toss the apples, celery & minced shallot with the lemon juice. Mix the sugar, walnuts, olive oil & salt & pepper. Then gently toss both mixtures together with the beetroot sticks. Place on the bed on lettuce and let sit for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Gluten Free too :)

fields.title: Recipes - Thai Cauliflower
fields.body_html:
Ingredients (serves 4)

1 tablespoon peanut oil
1 brown onion, thinly sliced
1 garlic clove, crushed
400ml can coconut cream
2 tablespoons Thai red curry paste
2 tablespoons Tamari
1 tablespoon lime juice
1 tablespoon sugar
600g cauliflower, trimmed, cut into florets
1 bunch green beans, cut into 5cm lengths
1/2 cup fresh coriander leaves, chopped
1 long red chilli, thinly sliced

Method

Heat a wok over high heat. Add oil. Swirl to coat. Add onion. Stir-fry until onion has softened. Add garlic. Stir-fry for another minute.


Spoon thick top layer of coconut cream into wok. Add curry paste. Cook, stirring, for a few minutes or until oil separates and rises to the top. Add fish sauce, lime juice, sugar and remaining coconut cream. Bring to the boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Add cauliflower and beans. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Transfer to a dish. Sprinkle with coriander serve.

This dish can be prepared in advance and is worth trying chilled. Yum!

It's also GLUTEN FREE

fields.title: Recipes - Zucchini Fritters
fields.body_html:
Ingredients (serves 4)

3 (about 400g) medium zucchini
1/2 cup self-raising flour
1/2 cup grated cheese
3 shallots, ends trimmed, thinly sliced
2 eggs, whisked
1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped
3 tablespoons fresh dill, chopped
1 tsp salt
1/4 tsp ground nutmeg
4 tsp olive oil


Method

Trim the ends from zucchini. Coarsely grate the zucchini. Place in a colander and squeeze out as much excess moisture as possible. Transfer to a bowl. Stir in self-raising flour, parmesan, shallots, egg, parsley, oregano, salt and nutmeg.


Heat 2 tsp olive oil in a non-stick frying pan over medium-high heat. Drop four 2-tablespoonful measures of zucchini mixture into pan. Cook for 1 1/2 minutes each side or until golden and cooked through. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel. Repeat with 2 tsp olive oil and remaining zucchini mixture.

GLUTEN FREE; Swap flour with gluten free flour and this recipe with work for you too!
